****
[3] Zhejiang, Jiangxi & Shandong (susp.) provinces
--------------------------------------------------
Date: Mon 22 Apr 2013
Source: English News, Xinhua News Agency [edited]
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/health/2013-04/22/c_132331013.htm


Another 2 cases of H7N9 bird flu were confirmed on Monday [22 Apr 2013] in east China's Zhejiang Province, bringing the province's total number of infections to 40, said local authorities.

The patients, a 54-year-old female office clerk from the provincial capital of Hangzhou and a 32-year-old farmer from the neighboring Jiangxi Province, are receiving treatment in 2 local hospitals [in Zhejiang], according to the provincial health department.

A 41-year-old patient, who tested positive for H7N9 on [17 Apr 2013], recovered and left hospital on Monday morning [22 Apr 2013], according to the department. So far in Zhejiang province, 5 people have died of H7N9 bird flu and 2 have been discharged from hospital after making a full recovery.

Shandong Province (suspected)
-----------------------------
A 36-year-old man suspected of being infected with H7N9 was found in Zaozhuang City of east China's Shandong Province on Monday [22 Apr 2013], the 1st case discovered in the province, according to the provincial health department. The man's sample has been sent to the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention for confirmation.

(By Chen Zhi)

